    "body": "I've just finished my investigation, it seems we can use Lokalise both for the TS and JSON files at the same time. Lokalise is able to merge keys with different names but the same translations.\r\n\r\nThe process is as follows (_for the sake of simplification, I've used an only subset of strings from en and de translation files_) :\r\n1) Add translation files from both desktop and mobile\r\n![Screenshot from 2022-05-05 16-58-31](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/33099791/166957437-19006ada-d0ad-4095-9c15-a6bfeda330d1.png)\r\n2) Use \"Duplicate finder\" to merge all possible keys (follow step 2 from https://docs.lokalise.com/en/articles/1400512-merging-existing-ios-and-android-keys)\r\n![Screenshot from 2022-05-05 16-59-12](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/33099791/166957592-b6ed3473-9f0a-44b9-a9a2-a6508c136eac.png)\r\nIt will produce merged key entries, an example:\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/33099791/166958135-188dd560-f191-44f5-9291-5a52204cecd9.png)\r\n3) Export translated files .ts and .json (Lokalise is smart enough to keep original keys per platform)\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nThe above implies no custom scripts are needed anymore, current [6 steps translation process ](https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/blob/df784bc8c147667e262dc764d8dd5aa642ea082a/scripts/translationScripts/README.md#tldr) should be simplified to:\r\n1. Update *.ts files: `lupdate ../../ui/nim-status-client.pro`\r\n2. Upload *.ts files to Lokalise\r\n3. Download translated *.ts files from Lokalise\r\n4. Create translation binaries `lrelease ../../ui/i18n/*.ts`",
